  <prompt>
    Add a `JsonSchema` field (nullable string) to the `AnalysisTool` DTO + a corresponding
    Dataverse column on `sprk_analysistool`. The field stores the JSON Schema describing
    the tool's parameter shape for LLM function-calling. Nullable for playbook-only tools
    (Playbook context); required for chat-available tools (`Chat` or `Both`).

    Critical-path context: this field feeds the `ToolHandlerToAIFunctionAdapter` (task 010)
    which wraps an `IToolHandler` as a `Microsoft.Extensions.AI.AIFunction` â€” the LLM
    sees the JSON Schema as the function's parameter declaration. Without this field,
    chat-side tool invocation cannot be generated from data; we'd be back to hardcoded
    tool classes. The Q9 batch migration (task 012) populates this field on every migrated
    chat tool row.

    Dataverse column: multi-line text (~64KB max), nullable. DTO: nullable string + JSON
    validation helper. Add unit tests covering: valid JSON Schema parses cleanly; null is
    permitted; invalid JSON raises at validation time (not silently passed to LLM).
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior BFF engineer experienced with JSON Schema validation, the `sprk_analysistool`
    entity, and the AI function-calling parameter contract.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `AnalysisTool` DTO has `JsonSchema` (nullable string) field; `sprk_analysistool` entity
    has matching multi-line text column. DTO + column persist a valid JSON Schema. Unit
    tests cover null-allowed + valid-JSON-required + invalid-JSON-rejected cases.
    Build green; publish-size delta reported.
  </goal>

